<name>DIAGNOSTIC TROUBLE CODE CHART</name>
<subpara id="RM000001JB2002X_z0" proc-id="RM0250U___00000ZG00000">
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<atten3>
<ptxt>Turn the ignition switch off before removing parts.</ptxt>
</atten3>
<atten4>
<list1 type="unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>If no abnormality is found when inspecting parts, inspect the skid control ECU and ground points for poor contact.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>If a malfunction code is displayed during the DTC check, check the circuit indicated by the DTC. For details of each code, refer to the "See page" for respective "DTC No." in the DTC chart.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>When 2 or more DTCs are detected, perform circuit inspection one by one until the problem is identified.</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</atten4>
